Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Quiet small but this establishment was one of the best coffeeshops I visited in Amsterdam. VERY friendly staff, nice and chilly music and good herbs. Love it.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Nice place and good ganja. Too bad about the unfriendly staff. After buying a smoke and sitting down we were told that we had to buy a drink to stay inside. Never heard of this, from a coffee shop I want good weed not a sugary drink.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Popped in and they had run out of alot but still had something to smoke. Thry also told us the coffee machine was broken too, we wasn't after one anyway. Very small place with high ceilings and clientele. They have like a little snug area in the corner at the back which was nice but could of done with larger seats I'd say.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Loved this coffeeshop, very nice interior with suitably creative decor and a nice little outdoor seating area where we spent afternoons relaxing in the sun. Excellent selection of strains and nice coffee to boot.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Usually I never give 5 stars, but today I had a faboulus experience in this small Green House in Waterlooplein. They have the real and original Jack Herrer (not easy to find bcz is not a modern hybrid strain), I bought also 1gr of amnesia ‚Ä¶

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Nice little find. Good selection of weed and hash and the coffee is great. Staff also very helpful.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: My favourite coffeeshop in Amsterdam. The staff is lovely and the strains are good. Highly recommend for first time visitors.

Name: Green House Namaste

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: Great products, nice shop, friendly staff. A perfect place to stop before and after visiting the nearby Waterlooplein Market.   I miss the old feel of the shop before they remodeled. I used to sit at the table by the front window and watch the people going by. The remodel is quite nice though, and still a comfortable space.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: This was the first place we visited in Amsterdam and it was a good start. We arrived at the end of Kings Day, but the staff were still super friendly and helpful. The decor is really chilled out and we had a great hour or so in there. Nice little place to stop in.

Name: Green House Namaste
Review Text: A tidy little shop hiding next to a restaurant. Refurbished since my last visit, the seating area is more sofa and coffee table than chairs with tables. No more sitting at the counter either. The layout is neater, more visibly organised ‚Ä¶
